Software Sustainability Evaluation Pipeline - Replication Guide

Purpose
Reproduce datasets and analysis artifacts from the study using the same repository
cohort and environment settings.

Data provenance and ethics
- Inputs are public open-source repositories configured in `pipeline/configs/config.py`.
- The pipeline analyzes source code and git history.
- No private data is intentionally collected.
- Respect upstream repository licenses and terms.

Reproduction steps (end-to-end)
1) Configure environment variables
   - Edit `configs/env.ps1` (PowerShell) or `configs/env.sh` (Bash).
   - Set:
     SONAR_HOST_URL, SONAR_TOKEN
     LLM_PROVIDER, LLM_MODEL, LLM_BASE_URL
     LLM_API_KEY (for hosted APIs)

2) Optional clean rerun
   - Remove previous outputs in `data/results/`.

3) Run the core pipeline
   python -m pipeline.main

4) Optional validation
   - Set `VALIDATE_OUTPUTS=true` before running, or run:
     python -m pipeline.validate_outputs

5) Optional research analyses
   python -m analysis.rq_process_sustainability
   python -m analysis.rq_visualizations
   python -m analysis.rq1_analysis.scripts.rq1_full_analysis

Core outputs
- data/results/git/git_metrics.csv
- data/results/sonar/sonar_metrics.csv
- data/results/llm/llm_metrics_<model>_runNNN.csv
- data/results/merged/final_dataset.csv

Optional outputs
- data/results/validation/validate_report.json
- data/results/holistic/holistic_assessments_<model>_runNNN.csv
- analysis/rq1_analysis/figures/*.png
- analysis/rq1_analysis/tables/*.csv
- analysis/rq2_analysis/figures/*.png

Reproducibility notes
- Git metrics are deterministic for a fixed repo HEAD and time window.
- Outputs include timestamp and commit metadata for traceability.
- LLM outputs are stochastic; use same model/version and prompts to reduce variance.
